description: Ghoul visits Doctor Rachel Deming, the only other survivor of the Exiles, and she informs him where the Exiles are buried. Ghoul visits the cemetery and tries to communicate with their souls, but too much time has passed and can only catch glimmers of his former teammates. He confides that he senses death around his new teammate, Pixx, and wants to try to save her. He then goes to meet with the rest of Ultraforce at the White House, where they have a meeting with the President of the United States of America. While Prototype, Prime and Prototype are well known to the public, the other members of Ultraforce inform the President who they are and give a brief origin. With the President's blessing, Ultraforce addresses the public by stating their mission of providing confidence to the public that ultras are taking responsible for themselves and that they are going to stop Atalon from capturing more nuclear weapons and to retrieve the ones he has already stolen. When they all arrive on Contrary's airship, Hardcase sends the members of Ultraforce to recruit other known ultras including Mantra, the Strangers, the Solution and Night Man. Meanwhile, Contrary continues to manipulate the members of Ultraforce for her own machinations of power. In the middle of Hardcase negotiating with the Strangers, Contrary teleports him back to the airship to inform him of Atalon's recent attack on Russian military bases. Before long, Contrary's manipulations backfire and a big fight occurs on her airship. Prototype and Prime want to go to Russia without their government's support but Hardcase forbids them, which starts the fight. After the fight, Prime feels betrayed and leaves the team. Atalon attacks a Russian nuclear submarine and builds an island with his gravitational powers, which will provide a base for his people, the Fire People.
name: Collision Course

description: Atalon uses his massive gravity-altering abilities to erect an island very close to Cuba. This event causes havoc all across the world, causing boats to capsize and shores to be struck by turbulent waves. Considering this move an act of war, the leaders of the world make plans for retaliation. The President of the United States of America sends Ultraforce to handle this for themselves. Ultraforce, without Prime who recently left, go directly to the new island to stop Atalon and his mad move for power. Hardcase immediately moves into his leadership role, sending orders to the members of Ultraforce. While Pixx, an electronics genius, tries to figure a way to dismantle the warheads, the rest of the team attacks Atalon and the Fire People. Atalon learns that Ghoul can speak to the dead and uses his power to bring Ghoul to him. While Ultraforce tries to save Ghoul, Pixx goes off to dismantle a solitary missle that was less loose from the stockpile. Prototype gets to the missile first and dismantles it, under the guidance of Pixx. The airships begin to falter because of Atalon's gravity and Prime shows up to save his teammates, making apologies for how he acted before. With the team reassembled, Hardcase states how they have to defeat Atalon immediately when a giant explosion occurs in the ocean.
name: Head To Head

description: Atalon kidnaps Ghoul so that he can communicate with the founds of the Fire People, who are long dead. Atalon forces Ghoul to concentrate and to Ghoul's surprise, he makes contact. While they learn the history of the Fire People, Ultraforce tries to quell the anxiety of the public, who feel that ultras are to blame for the world's latest conflict. Ultraforce goes to the headquarters that the government has created for them to devise a plan to defeat Atalon. Contrary is able to formulate a plan that calls for Pixx to manually dismantle all the warheads while the rest of Ultraforce take the fight to Atalon directly. Meanwhile, Atalon starts his own plan of conquering the world.
name: Ghosts

description: Ultraforce attacks Atalon to finally stop his assault against Earth. While Pixx uses her illusionary abilities to get to the warheads, the rest of Ultraforce attacks Atalon and his forces as a diversion. While searching the warheads, Pixx finds Ghoul, who takes her to the warheads. A member of Atalon's forces finds Pixx and Ghoul and is able to destroy Pixx's containment suit, meant to protect her against the radiation of the warheads. Feeling that her life is worth the sacrifice she continues to dismantle each warheads while being irradiated. Atalon finally realizes that the battle against him was just a diversion and gives up the fight, knowing the warheads have been taken care of, but not at a price: Pixx is dead.
name: Last Stand

description: Finding Pixx dead, Ultraforce makes an all out final assault against Atalon, venting their grief against the mad despot. Contrary is able to retrieve her airship from underwater while everything occurred on Atalon's island and uses it to handle Atalon's forces. As a final act, Atalon uses his unbelivable power over gravity to set in motion the destruction of the planet. Before he can accomplish his goal, Atalon is teleported onto Contrary's ship, where she speaks to him to decide a better fate for everyone. Their discussion causes Atalon to stop his chain of destruction and he comes to an accordance with Contrary and then the leaders of various countries. Using the island he created as a base, Atalon becomes the King of his island, living on the surface as a nation.
name: Final Blow

description: Ghoul assists in an apparent suicide case that is then suspected of being a murder case.
name: Mosh Pit!

description: Prime and Prototype fly towards the Ultraforce headquarters when Prototype hears over the police scanner that there's an apparent ultra creating trouble. Prime and Prototype arrive to find the Black Knight from the Marvel Universe defending himself from some police officers, searching for Sersi. After a brief fight they go to Ultraforce's headquarters. Black Knight explains to Prototype and Prime that he comes from a different universe and he's searching for his love, Sersi. He also explains that he is a superhero from his world, and is a member of the Avengers. Suddenly, Siren arrives at the headquarters, claiming to be their newest member, and explains that she needs help. Black Knight assists and they go to a laboratory where beings of light begin to attack. Other members of Ultraforce arrive but cannot find a way to stop these beings of light, whom some call 'angels'. One of the 'angels' attacks Prime and seems to possess him. Meanwhile, it is revealed that Sersi also arrived on the planet but in Africa and seemingly possessed with a malignant intent.
name: Heaven On Earth

description: Black Knight learns that the 'angels' that are currently attacking people on the street are actually forms of energy that expand and multiply when close to bio-energy. Since Ghoul is technically dead, the 'angels' turn immobile when he grabs them, so he becomes Ultraforce's weapon against them. Ultraforce, with the help of Black Knight, place the 'angels' in containment units and save the day. Meanwhile, Sersi finds an Infinity Gem and loses herself, but is able to latch on the memory of Black Knight. She sees him on television with Ultraforce and goes to find him.
name: Let There Be Light

description: Alec fights a gang of murderous thugs in a city that isn't quite real.
Rafferty torments Firearm with murder after murder.
name: Rafferty: In His Own Words

description: Firearm marries his beloved before setting off to destroy Rafferty; the man has taken an entire church hostage.
name: Alec Swan's Best Day
Double Dangerous/ The Destiny trail Prologue.

description:

The story is continued in Prime annual 1
name: Up Against The Wall!
Hungry For Heroes! (Or a sandwich to die for!)
One-Two Punch

description:
Jack's tour of the USA continues and he's about to discover that he's not the only when a strange secret. When Jack encounters a enigmatic drifter with the power to summon the past, will Shadowman be able to survive the ghosts that come calling?

1st appearance:

- R. L. McNeely
name: April Visions

description:
Shadowman takes Manhattan! The Big Easy meets the Big Apple when Jack lands the gig of a lifetime. But this is one concrete jungle where it's not safe to play, even when you wield the power of the legendary Shadowman!

1st appearance:

- Carmen Ruiz

- Hwen Fong (Dr. Mirage)
name: A Bite Of The Apple

description:
New Orleans' new protectors are...Archer & Armstrong?! Valiant's mismatched adventurers have been drawn to the Big Easy by Master Darque, but to what end? Plus-- what secret of the Shadowman legacy is waiting for Jack in the backwaters bayou of Louisiana?

1st appearance:

- Leiland Paige
name: Convergence

description: Deep in the bayou with Archer & Armstrong, Jack Boniface is going to have his demon exorcised! But when the force that drives him out into the night is gone will there be anything left of the Shadowman? And without Shadowman can they survive the Nazi servitors of Master Darque come to make the bayou a living hell!
name: Exorcism

description: Jack Boniface is living the dream and jamming with Aerosmith! But when one fan turns to the necromancy of Master Darque to make his dream of playing with the band come true, Shadowman will have to take the stage to save Steven Tyler from playing his last gig as a Bloodrunner!
name: Darque Desires

description: A dream draws Jack Boniface back to the old homestead, where old secrets refuse to stay buried. Snake-handling preacher Josiah Torrent is back and the power of the Master is in him... Master Darque that is! Can Shadowman save his parents or will the secret they've kept from him destroy them all?
name: Sins Of The Fathers

description:
To save his mother's life Jack Boniface has sworn the services of Shadowman to Master Darque, and now it's time for Darque to collect! When Darque sends Jack sliding backwards and forwards through time he'll see the future he's inspired and the past that haunts him. But will the legacy of the Shadowman save him, or be his end?

1st appearance:

- Blister

- Calvin

Original color art (see pic below).
name: Time Slidin'

description: Shadowman is back in time and face to face with... Shadowman! And he's got a sword to Nettie's throat! Face to face with the past and trying to save the future, will Jack abandon his last chance at being with Elya to thwart Darque's master plan or will he stay lost in time forever?
name: Again And Again And Again

description:
Master Darque's time tunnel sends Jack back to 1890's New Orleans, where he faces the Shadowman of that era, Maxim St. James. Meanwhile, in the present, Dr. Mirage attempts to save both Jack and himself from the machinations of Darque.

(Continued from Dr. Mirage #5)
name: Didn't He Ramble?

description:
Against the forces of HATE! Jack is ensnared in a web of political hatred when he accepts an invitation to speak on talk radio. Tragedy, and a moment of blind rage, causes Shadowman to rethink his mission.

1st appearance:

- Rotwak
name: H.A.T.E.

description: Jack hunts a murderer on the streets of New Orleans, but the only path to capturing the killer is inside Shadowman's dreams.
name: A Nightmare On Bourbon Street

description:
It's Mardi Gras -- and in the hands of Ishmael, these beads are deadly! On the trail of a thief, a mysterious cabal turns the tables and Shadowman quickly finds himself in an unusual position as hunter becomes hunted.

1st appearance:

- Marcia

- Papa Napoleon

- Ishmael
name: Glitter Night

description: Shadowman has had a lead pipe rammed through his chest. While recovering from a sizable exit wound at the New Orleans State Hospital, Papa Napoleon sends Ishmael to finish him off.
name: The Morning After

description: As Jack Boniface attempts to rebuild his life, Shadowman steels himself for a confrontation with Master Darque.
name: Something Coming

description: On the trail of a vicious drug pusher, another innocent learns Shadowman's secret identity. But there's more than one monster lurking in the dark of New Orleans.
name: Aftermath

description: Shadowman faces off against Darque's latest necromantic creation -- a soul-thirsty amalgamation of the dead called The Night Monster.
name: Hunger

description:
Consumed by the Night Monster, Shadowman meets a skeletal wise man from an Edwardian world within. Now that Sandria has achieved godhood, does she stand a chance against the beast, or must she risk sharing her divinity with a familiar foe?

1st appearance:

- Baron Zastrow

- Elwood
name: In The Belly Of The Beast

description:
As the souls of the dead burst forth and revolt, the Night Monster's reign of terror comes to an explosive conclusion -- but another evil is waiting to rise from under the black channels of the Bayou.

1st appearance:

- Luis Rojas
name: Quest

description: A Colombian drug cartel has taken Nettie captive for her voodoo power! But will these corrupt men get more than they bargained for?! And will Shadowman be able to save the day?!
name: Song For The Dead

description: When an innocent bystander witnesses a horrific crime, it's Shadowman's job to protect her - before it is too late!
name: Cinderella Blues

description: Will Shadowman be able to save his damsel in distress before it's too late?! And will he be able to take down the killer for hire called Ishmael for good?
name: Cinderella Blues - Part 2: Flames Of Rage

description: What mysterious reason put Shadowman on a collision path with X-O Manowar? Will these two heroes see eye to eye or become mortal enemies? And when Aric loses control of the X-O Manowar armor can even Shadowman survive the night?!
name: Aric

description: With the help of a mysterious woman, Aric regains control of the X-O Manowar armor. But will Shadowman be able to regain the upper hand against the hideous Blister?!
name: Wild Card

description: Will Shadowman be able to find and defeat Blister's devious employer - Ishmael. But what plans could Nettie possibly have for this killer for hire?
name: Funeral Rap

description: When a popular author becomes one of the monsters she so often writes about, can Shadowman save her from her fate? Or will she drink his life's blood?!
name: Undead Love

description: Shadowman is a wanted man! The police are looking to bring Jack Boniface in, the charge: of reckless endangerment of the citizens of New Orleans. Will he have to face the music for his alter ego?
name: Under Arrest

description: Jack Boniface is on trial for the crimes of Shadowman! Is it time Jack finally hung up the mask?
name: Nightcourt

description: Last issue!
name: The End?
